programme.title: Polar Immersion
programme.desc: Firmly beset in the grip of polar winter, an opportunity arises to study climate change above and beneath the ice sheet. Part scientific exploration, part shared existence with the Inuit, this human adventure reveals the never-before-seen depths of this fascinating world in the throes of upheaval.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Join Alexandra as she visits with a friendly, forward-thinking family in Las Vegas, Nevada, a city certainly not built on winners (unless you become one), where anything is possible, and where water is so much of a precious resource the city employs water waste investigators.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Renaissance Europe
programme.desc: Travelers adore Italy, and Italy adores the Renaissance. In this historical half-hour, we follow Western Europe's transitiical sites and museums in favor of a trip--or a day--just for fun.

programme.title: Europe's Getaways
programme.desc: A key attraction of travel on any continent, including Europe, is that 30 minutes outside any city exists a getaway unlike any you will find on the globe. Truly unique locations that resonate with history and significance. Here, we explore a few such places.

programme.title: Ireland's West Coast
programme.desc: Our trip to Ireland's west coast begins in Galway, Europe's fastest growing city, shopping for Irish crystal and Celtic jewelry. Then it is a salt-sprayed trip to the fabled Aran Islands where we reach breathless heights at a Stone Age fort and ferret out traditional hand-knit sweaters.

programme.title: Dublin and Beyond
programme.desc: Irish eyes are smiling when we explore Dublin, Ireland's urban core. There is history around every corner, and Dublin delights with Trinity College, the Book of Kells, the famous Guinness Brewery, and the infamous Kilmainham jail where Irish rebels spent their last days.

programme.title: Germany's Romantic Road
programme.desc: The Romantic Road winds through some of Germany's most picturesque countryside complete with medieval villages and Baroque Palaces. We start our journey in Wurzburg where we visit the spectacular Baroque Bishop's Palace or Residenz and taste wine at one of Wurzburg's many wine festivals.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Thailand, The Andaman Islands
programme.desc: Andaman Coast towns such as Phuket are well known to backpackers and sun seekers. Join Rudy as he paddles through hidden entrances of small islands to find mangroves few people ever see. Also, visit the dramatic limestone cliffs and rock formations jutting out from translucent waters of Phang-nga Bay.

programme.title: Estonia
programme.desc: Venture to Estonia and the islands of Saaremaa and Muhu where you will find windmills, thatch-roofed farmhouses, and quiet waters. Rudy interviews Mart Laar who took over Estonia under tough conditions following the withdrawal of Soviet troops and turned it into a dynamic country.

programme.title: St. Petersburg, Russia
programme.desc: From the splendors of Peterhof to the quiet grace of the city's canals, this former capital built by a czar has reclaimed its position as one of the world's great destinations. St. Petersburg--enjoying a renaissance since its favorite son, Vladimir Putin, ascended to office—has lifted its gloom.

programme.title: Buenos Aires, Argentina
programme.desc: The style and verve of one of South America's most beautiful capitals is highlighted with Argentina's national dance, the tango, as well as the energy that its diverse population brings to the urban landscape. Discover a very special place in Buenos Aires.

programme.title: Mendoza, Argentina
programme.desc: As Rudy ascends into the thin air of the Andes, he stops to visit the graveyard of those who died climbing Aconcagua. Rudy’s next choice for high-altitude adventure? Getting soaked whitewater rafting. Back at sea level he meets winemakers whose elegant Malbecs are shaking up the world's wine market.

programme.title: India: From Girl to Woman
programme.desc: “First marriage and then love.” This Indian proverb describes Indian society quite accurately in terms of how the tradition of marriage is perceived and experienced in the country. In India, people do not just marry whoever they wish. It is the family that decides in an arrangement called Shaadi.

programme.title: Kyoto, Japan
programme.desc: The spiritual heart of Japan, Kyoto offers a glimpse of Japanese life as it used to be, primarily because it was spared during World War II. Comfortable streets with wooden homes, impressive temples, and a dedication to ancient Japanese traditions make Kyoto one of Japan's most visited cities.

programme.title: Yosemite America's Treasure
programme.desc: Experience Yosemite's breathtaking icons like the granite monoliths El Capitan and Half Dome and behold the splendor of Bridal Veil and Yosemite Falls. Explore Yosemite's deep history as the first land set aside for preservation, and a land that inspired John Muir and photographer Ansel Adams.

programme.title: Portugal's Via Publicae
programme.desc: Open your ears to those who call this land home, and who will unveil its unique characteristics to you. Via Publicae was once an ancient Roman road and trade route that stretched from Braga in the north to Lisbon in the south of Portugal. Roman influence was once very strong in this region.

programme.title: From Ouagadougou to Conakry: The Road of Possibility
programme.desc: In Burkina Faso, Mali, and Guinea, explore the “Africa of Possibility.” This is a continent with solutions, thanks to crafty people and their capacity to adapt. The Road of Possibility is more than journey from Ouagadougou to Conakry. On these tricky roads, obstacles trigger unique encounters.

programme.title: Fiji - Island Flavors
programme.desc: The Fijian Archipelago consists of more than 300 islands scattered across the South Pacific Ocean. In Fiji, everyone can find an island that suits them, as you retrace the trail of Robinson Crusoe in this incredible paradise.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: The French Laundry Experience
programme.desc: Napa, CA: Marooned in San Francisco, Tony tastes local shellfish and durian ice cream before embarking on a pilgrimage to experience the genius of Thomas Keller, chef and owner of The French Laundry.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Mt. Rushmore and the Black Hills
programme.desc: Mount Rushmore stands unrivaled in the world, a sky-high tribute to the heroes and ideals that shaped America. This stirring program features rare footage that chronicles its monumental construction. This iconic treasure is just one of the wonders to be found in the stoic Black Hill’s region.

programme.title: S8E4 - Presenting: World-Class Wines of Baja
programme.desc: Join Rick and winemaker Hugo d’Acosta as they toast the world-class wines of Baja California Norte. Hugo first introduces Rick his Casa de Piedra wines before moving on to Tres Mujeres, L.A. Cetto, and the San Rafael Winery.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: The Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Begin your stay along the Amalfi Coast in stunning Positano. They say Ravello is a town suspended between sea and sky, and it will leave an impression on you as it has on many artists, musicians, and writers. In Salerno, the gardens at Villa Rufolo will seer into your memory.

programme.title: Genoa and the Italian Riviera
programme.desc: We are off to the Italian Riviera seeking la dolce vita in one of the world's most romantic locations. With awe-inspiring cliffs, and beaches that shimmer like jewels on the Mediterranean, the Riviera is as stunning a coastline as anywhere in Europe.

programme.title: Adelaide, Part 1
programme.desc: Spend the entire day on Kangaroo Island, as Jason gets adventurous in Adelaide. We will learn to make our own blend of wine at Penfolds, while also taking in breathtaking views as we glide over Barossa in a hot-air balloon.

programme.title: S8E8 - Italy's Verona, Padova, and Ravenna
programme.desc: We'll visit three great cities in the shadow of Venice: Padova (Padua), with its university life and famed basilica; Verona and its Roman ruins; and Ravenna, for its shimmering mosaics.

programme.title: Part 2
programme.desc: Travel to the Pinar del Rio and visit the lush tobacco fields that produce the most sought-after cigars in the world. As you explore further, colorful towns and sugar plantations unfold before your eyes. Walk the beaches of Matanzas and Cuba’s colorful coastline. Cuban people welcome visitors with open arms, and their blend of cultures overflow with friendly and easy-going hospitality.

programme.title: Savannah
programme.desc: We visit the old South and enjoy some sweet tea in Savannah. On this episode, we will stroll the city’s beautiful squares, as well as visit its civil war past at Old Fort Jackson. Then, we head up the stairs of the famous Tybee Island lighthouse and visit the Savannah Railroad museum.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: Light Beneath the Arctic
programme.desc: Ghislain and Emmanuelle Bardout and the U.T.P. team take you on a fresh expedition through the Northwest Passage, revealing a mythical seaway that symbolizes the very evolution of the polar world. The team will dive into the “twilight zone” to find the first biofluorescent Arctic species.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Join Alexandra as she visits with a friendly, forward-thinking family in Las Vegas, Nevada, a city certainly not built on winners (unless you become one), where anything is possible, and where water is so much of a precious resource the city employs water waste investigators.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Prague
programme.desc: Explore the heart of Bohemia as we join Laura in Prague. Visit Prague Castle, the Charles Bridge, and the Jewish Quarter. Gothic Loket Castle is a short, scenic drive away from the city and worth the tour. Next up the must-see spa town of Karlovy Vary.

programme.title: Britain's Historic Countryside
programme.desc: First stops are Camden Market and Notting Hill Gate. Enjoy a treat as Laura escorts you to the birthplace of pomp and circumstance, Buckingham Palace. Then mosey down to Windsor Castle before taking on London with Big Ben and Tower Bridge.

programme.title: Ireland
programme.desc: Ireland is a country filled with tradition, culture, and history, and here you will feel outright the pride of the Celts as you visit Blarney and Ashford Castles, learn of Francis Mahoney, meet the Guinness family, and tour the Irish School of Falconry.

programme.title: Chiang-Mai
programme.desc: Explore Chiang Mai's "Night Bazaar" that hums with business, and its Buddhist Temples. When Laura visits the Maesa Elephant Camp, she is not just meeting a majestic animal, but an icon. Finally, join Laura ventures into Northern Thailand.

programme.title: Life Down Under
programme.desc: Laura McKenzie means business when she says that Queenstown is the “adventure capital of the world.” Located on the shores of beautiful Lake Wakatipu, Queenstown is surrounded by “the Remarkables,” mountains in the center of New Zealand's South Island.

programme.title: Puerto Rico
programme.desc: First, Laura will take us to San Juan, one of the largest natural harbors in the Caribbean. In Puerto Rico, the weather's warm year-round and the ocean water is heavenly. While the islands are Americanized, they also still retain their Hispanic culture.

programme.title: Italy: Part 2
programme.desc: The brilliance and grandeur of Italy is demonstrated in five captivating settings. Feel like a tall wildflower in the sun and breeze as the hills of Altomonte billow off into the distance, sooth every aching nerve as you absorb the perfect view along the Tiber River, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Underwater Beauty
programme.desc: Fish of all stripes and fluorescence call the crystal-clear waters of Chicago’s Shedd Aquarium home. Water and light collaborate to reveal the tranquil beauty that is life underwater.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Kyushu
programme.desc: Explore the island of Kyushu with it's dramatic landscape and hot sands, and discover the essence of Japanese cuisine with Daisuke Utagawa and Rudy Maxa.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Tokyo
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa and Daisuke Utagawa take us to the heart of Japan in Tokyo where culinary geniuses strive for perfection as they prepare everything from sushi to the wasabi.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Hokkaido
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa and Daisuke Utagawa take you to Japan's northern frontier Hokkaido. The hot spring capital of Japan with its many volcanoes, Hokkaido also boosts some of the world greatest ramen, ramen noodles, and legendary whiskey.

programme.title: Hong Kong, Part 1
programme.desc: Host Rudy Maxa and Washington, D.C. restaurateur and chef Daisuke Utagawa enthusiastically eat their way through Hong Kong, from cheap but authentic, hole-in-the-wall Chinese restaurants to Michelin-starred palaces. Along the way they illustrate the excitement and energy that defines Hong Kong.

programme.title: Hong Kong, Part 2
programme.desc: Dramatic photography by renowned shooters Karel Bauer and Joe Pontecorvo bring Hong Kong into viewers' homes as never before. Stray from the iconic photo of Hong Kong as a wall of skyscrapers against Victoria Peak with the city's harbor in a foreground and visits the other side of the island.

programme.title: Bangkok
programme.desc: Washington, DC, restaurateur Daisuke Utagawa and travel journalist Rudy Max deliver viewers directly to Bangkok’s sprawling city temples, its huge flower market, its vibrant klongs (canals), and to its most interesting cuisine, all of which made Bangkok the world’s most-visited city by travelers.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: Wild National Parks
programme.desc: From grizzly bears of Katmai National Park in Alaska to rattlesnakes of Montezuma's Castle in Arizona, answer the call of America's wildest national parks. By land, sea, and sky, get up close to creatures of all shapes and sizes. Dedicated park workers reveal what it takes to nurture nature.

programme.title: The Mohawk Trail Across New England
programme.desc: The Mohawk Trail is deeply embedded in the history of America. For many years it served as a main trade route for indigenous tribes. As European settlement expanded, the Mohawk Trail began to change as the country itself changed. Tap into one of America’s richest springs of historical significance.

programme.title: Brazil: The Road of Conquered Lands
programme.desc: Brazil is toooften reduced to its wild samba, magical football, and endless beaches. Behind this fantasy lurks an economic colossus, agricultural titan, and a force in geopolitical affairs. Travel routes taken by the original colonists, from the Atlantic coast deep into the Amazonian forest.

programme.title: Mozambique - An African Dawn
programme.desc: Known as the "land of good people," Mozambique offers some of the most wonderful outdoor experiences possible in Southern Africa, including the ability to explore the country's incredibly rich underwater marine parks.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: My Hometown Favorites
programme.desc: New York, NY: Passionate about his city, Tony gives us an intimate tour of the New York City foods he loves - sturgeon and bagels, fluke ceviche, pan-seared foie gras, braised veal cheek, authentic cheese and, of course, a hotdog.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Best Freaks of Nature
programme.desc: If you like your nature a little weird, then this is the show for you. See all the freaks of nature in the best parks ever.

programme.title: Hottest Parks
programme.desc: Volcanoes erupt and geysers explode in this sizzling episode. Take a look at the hottest parks you can visit!

programme.title: S8E5 - Eat Like a Local in Los Cabos
programme.desc: Ever travel to a tourist mecca and wonder what the locals eat? Join Rick and his friend Hugo to find the best Mexican food in Los Cabos. First stop is the municipal market in San Jose del Cabo, then they enjoy carnitas at Los Michoacanos.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Malta
programme.desc: A delightful Mediterranean climate, fantastic beaches, and fascinating historic sites only begin to describe the Maltese experience. Few places in the world possess a more exquisite coastline. The HBO series, "Game of Thrones," filmed portions of the series in Malta's capital city of Valletta.

programme.title: Florence
programme.desc: In this glorious Italian city, rich in history and art, Rudy brings the Renaissance to life. We visit the great museums - the Uffizi, Bargello, and Accademia, as well as the landmarks of the Renaissance - the Duomo, Baptistry and Giotto's Tower.

programme.title: Adelaide, Part 2
programme.desc: Captivated by South Australia's incredible beauty, Jason continues his Australian expedition along historic Hahndorf Main Street as he explores Adelaide’s Central Market and the Adelaide Festival Centre.

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Havana's Spirit
programme.desc: Cuban ingenuity and creativity are alive in Cuba’s capital of Havana, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. A leading site for fashion and music, Havana is reconnecting with its past as a starlet. Santiago de Cuba, the birthplace of Cuban music, is also featured. Experience “La Cubania.”

programme.title: St. Augustine
programme.desc: First, we will take a sip from the distinctively tasting Fountain of Youth. Then we will touch the coquina walls of the undefeated Castillo San Marcos. Next, separate pirate truth from pirate myth at the appropriately named, Pirate Museum, and cure what ails us at the oldest General Store.

programme.title: S7E5 - Florentine Delights and on exciting Tuscan Side Trips
programme.desc: We enjoy Renaissance art in Florence, the city that propelled Europe out of the Middle Ages. Then we visit two cultural capitals in their own right: Pisa, where we’ll marvel at a tipsy tower; and Lucca, where we’ll celebrate Puccini.

programme.title: Deep Sea Corals of Polynesia
programme.desc: Join the U.T.P. team to the Polynesian Islands as they lead a scientific team to unveil the coral reefs of the deep. After setting new records in diving within Arctic waters, Ghislain and Emmanuelle Bardout study how these reefs function, with the hope of capturing on film the corals spawning.

programme.title: Chinguetti
programme.desc: Once at a crossroads of ancient trade routes, the ksar of Chinguetti, Mauritania exists like a pearl in the desert on the western edge of the Sahara Desert, a force of nature whose sand reaches every crook and crevice of life in this land.

programme.title: Tamales and Iguana, Oaxacan Style
programme.desc: Oaxaca, Mexico: Chef Tony Bourdain explores the exotic and colorful indigenous zone of Mexico's Oaxaca region where he tastes toasted grasshoppers and other delicacies. His adventure ends with mariachi music and, of course, lots of tequila.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: San Francisco
programme.desc: Stroll down Grant Street with Laura into the heart of America's largest Chinatown. Bike, drive, or walk across the Golden Gate Bridge, the city's most recognizable landmark. Finally, Fisherman's Wharf offers day trips all wrapped into one fun location.

programme.title: Versailles
programme.desc: Enter 12 miles of enclosing walls, 26 acres of roof, and over 2,000 windows and experience the royal Palace of Versailles. If you are looking for some good ole' fun, then you will enjoy Parc Asterix. Place Vendome is the top spot for high-end merchandise.

programme.title: Gold Coast Australia
programme.desc: If you like sun, surf, sand, and a laid-back lifestyle then join Laura on Australia's Gold Coast. Travel into the thick of the Queensland Rainforest, and visit the home of the largest collection of Australian native animals in the Carrumbin Wildlife Sanctuary.

programme.title: Sicily
programme.desc: Begin on the east coast in Taormina. Laura then takes us to some of Sicily's highlight cities, Palermo and Randazzo. How about a visit to Agrigento, or to the divinely inspired Cathedral Monreale? We will also visit Mt. Etna, an active volcano.

programme.title: Venice
programme.desc: Begin with a tour down the Grand Canal, "the finest street in the world." Next, the pedestrian streets around the Rialto Bridge are lined with shops, and St. Mark's Basilica is one of the oldest and most beautiful Byzantine cathedrals in all of Europe.

programme.title: Oahu, Hawaii
programme.desc: Have a blast with Laura on this Hawaiian voyage as you explore sensational surf and beaches, unique Hawaiian culture and food, and climb volcanic mountains. Join Laura as she visits historic landmarks, such as the Iolani Palace and the Bishop Museum.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Village of Swimming Cows
programme.desc: What happens when eco-minded, city-dwelling Berliners move in with Polish farmers in the country? Take a charming, extraordinarily funny look at how friendship and communication can overcome boundaries, and how nourishing the mind, body, and spirit begins with love and respect for Mother Earth.

programme.title: Papua New Guinea: The Fire Dance
programme.desc: When a person dies, or to celebrate a harvest or important visit, the Baining tribesmen create masks representing the Spirit of the Forest. A great fire is then lit in the village, and dancers adorning the masks dance around the fire, jumping on the embers to prove they are stronger than the flames.

programme.title: Peru: Masters of Chaos
programme.desc: Anthropologist Anne-Sylvie Malbrancke journeys to meet Jenny, a young Peruvian who has crossed the country to ask the sacred lakes to heal her medical issue. For more than 700 years, shamans have drawn their power to heal from the Huaringas, sacred lagoons located on the border of Peru and Ecuador.

programme.title: Amazonia: Becoming a Man
programme.desc: In the heart of the Amazon rainforest of Brazil, the Satere-Mawe people have a rite of passage leading to adulthood where a feat of bravery turns boys into men. According to tribe members, this painful initiation prepares young men for life and proves they can fulfill their reproductive obligations.

programme.title: Running of the Bulls
programme.desc: The Festival of San Fermin in Pamplona, Spain is a deeply rooted celebration of traditional and folkloric events, including the Running of the Bulls. Experience the incredible energy each morning for eight consecutive days as thousands of people run ahead of six, 2,000-pound charging bulls.

programme.title: S8E1 - Mediterranean Baja
programme.desc: The Baja California peninsula boasts a climate reminiscent of the Mediterranean Sea. Rick makes tacos with ingredients from the gardens of the Rancho La Puerta spa, and meets up with Chefs Miguel Angel Guerrero Yagues and Jair Tellez.

programme.title: S8E2 - Tijuana Taco Crawl
programme.desc: Three local Tijuana foodies take Rick on a taco crawl. Experience arrachera tacos, suadero tacos, sauteed and fried shrimp tacos, steamed tacos, and smoked salmon tacos. At home, Rick creates a taco feast for a casual backyard cookout.

programme.title: S8E3 - Cooking on the Sea of Cortez
programme.desc: Rick is always up for a cooking challenge, and after a day on the waters of the Sea of Cortez, Rick grills dinner for the group on the beach of Espiritu Santo Island. To stock up on supplies Rick shops in the La Paz market for ingredients.

programme.title: S8E4 - Presenting: World-Class Wines of Baja
programme.desc: Join Rick and winemaker Hugo d’Acosta as they toast the world-class wines of Baja California Norte. Hugo first introduces Rick his Casa de Piedra wines before moving on to Tres Mujeres, L.A. Cetto, and the San Rafael Winery.

programme.title: S8E5 - Eat Like a Local in Los Cabos
programme.desc: Ever travel to a tourist mecca and wonder what the locals eat? Join Rick and his friend Hugo to find the best Mexican food in Los Cabos. First stop is the municipal market in San Jose del Cabo, then they enjoy carnitas at Los Michoacanos.

programme.title: S8E6 - A Delicious Feast in Magdalena Bay
programme.desc: Rick and local guide Luis Garduno of REDTours venture out on a skiff to learn about sustainable fishing on Magdalena Bay. They catch up with local lobster fishermen and clam divers and follow that up with shore lunch on Isla de Magdalena.

programme.title: S8E7 - Cooking in Wine Country
programme.desc: Ever dream of owning a winery? Don and Tru Miller made their dreams come true when they built Adobe Guadalupe. Rick’s dream of cooking in their stunning kitchen, with its handmade wood-fired oven, comes true this season. Dream on.

programme.title: S8E8 - Tijuana Round Table
programme.desc: There is a long heritage of good food in Tijuana. The city has an amazing taco, culture and is the birthplace of the Caesar salad. Today, Tijuana boasts one of the top culinary schools in the country and some of the best chefs in Mexico.

programme.title: S8E9 - Extraordinarily Delicious Ensenada
programme.desc: Fish tacos embody Ensenada’s history: Fresh fish from pristine waters encased in crispy batter influenced by Asian immigrants, topped with Spanish-inspired creamy sauces, wrapped in a very Mexican corn tortilla, and spiked with chile.

programme.title: S8E10 - Mexican Microbrews and Pub Fare
programme.desc: Many of us experienced our first Mexican beer on a beach with a squeeze of lime. Now we are happy to see a beer revolution rumbling in the Baja peninsula. Rick takes us from the Tecate brewery to the Tijuana brewery. Salud-

programme.title: S8E11 - Sustainable Aquaculture in the Rich Waters of Ensenada
programme.desc: Two of Ensenada’s best chefs, Benito Molina, and Alain Genchi, join Rick for a lesson in mollusk farming. Juan Carlos Lapuente takes the trio to the rich coastal waters to see oyster and mussel farming and learn why these waters thrive.

programme.title: S8E12 - Todos Santos Magic
programme.desc: There is magic in the charming Baja town of Todos Santos. It all starts at the roadside bar Art and Beer. Then Rick checks into the Hotel California before meeting with Sergio Jaurequi, as well as Chefs Dona Ramona and Dany Lamote.

programme.title: S8E13 - Baja Beach House Cooking
programme.desc: Rick introduces us to some of Los Cabos’ top chefs and their restaurants, then cooks dinner for them at a luxurious beach house. At dinner, Rick, Margarita, and the local chefs discuss the philosophy of cooking and dining together.

programme.title: S9E1 - Oaxaca's Most Magical Holiday
programme.desc: Rick takes us on a remarkable journey through Oaxaca City during the revered Dia de Los Muertos (Day of the Dead) holiday. Much preparation for the celebration takes place in October, and Rick gives us an insider’s look at the fiesta.

programme.title: S9E2 - Oaxaca's Live-Fire Cooking
programme.desc: Everything tastes better when cooked over a fire, at least that is the Oaxacan credo. From soup to barbacoa, fiery embers influence the flavor of Oaxaca’s food in just the right ways. Join Rick in Oaxaca, San Felipe Usila, and Zaachilla.

programme.title: S9E3 - Off the Beaten Path in Huatulco
programme.desc: Mexico's beaches glimmer with pristine perfection. Chef Rick Bayless takes us off the beaten path to find great food and even better beaches such as Playa Chahue and Playa Principal. You would be well-advised to follow his lead.

programme.title: S9E4 - Artisan Mescal
programme.desc: Mescal is experiencing a renaissance in Mexico and throughout the United States. Journey with Rick to witness firsthand how an Oaxacan distiller handcrafts this fine spirit renowned for its rich, smoky complexity and brightness.

programme.title: S9E5 - Oaxaca, the Land of Seven Moles
programme.desc: So many moles, so little time. Rick will focus on two moles while visiting the Seasons of My Heart Cooking School on the outskirts of Oaxaca City to explore Black Mole and Green Mole with school owner Susana Trilling and her students.

programme.title: S9E6 - Delicious Eco-Tourism
programme.desc: Ever on a quest to learn more about food, Rick even vacations with a food-oriented agenda. Join him in the mountains of Finca Las Nieves, with its artisanal coffee production and organic gardens, and learn about sustainable gardening.

programme.title: S9E7 - The Kernel of Deliciousness
programme.desc: The variety of corns available in Oaxaca boggles the mind and the taste buds. Rick introduces us to Amado Ramirez Leyva who believes that corn, domesticated some 9,000 years ago in Mexico, represents the very foundation of Mexican culture.

programme.title: S9E8 - Mercado Madness
programme.desc: “You are what you eat.” Brillat Savarin’s statement fuels Rick’s tour of the 21 de Noviembre market in downtown Oaxaca. We uncover the incredibly rich culture of the market and its role in the daily lives and meals of the local population.

programme.title: S9E9 - Oaxacan Cheese Primer
programme.desc: In Mexico, cheese is all about freshness, and fresh cheese is exactly what Rick has found in the village of Rojas where he and two local women turn uber-fresh milk from alfalfa-fed cows into queso fresco and salty quesillo (string cheese).

programme.title: S9E10 - Puerto Escondido: Living the Dream
programme.desc: Ever dream of renting a space with a kitchen in Mexico just to cook all the fresh fish you can eat? Rick lives the dream at Hotel Villas Carrizalillo in Puerto Escondido. With few culinary tools, and fresh ingredients, it is time to feast.

programme.title: America's Treasures: National Parks
programme.desc: A cinematic journey through the awe-inspiring landscapes, historic sites and untamed wilderness of America's most legendary outdoor playgrounds.

programme.title: United States of Sports
programme.desc: Copa90’s Eli and Timbsy and Love Island’s Josh Denzel go on a once-in-a-lifetime road trip. Then, the guys hit the Midwest for an unforgettable road trip through Detroit, Chicago and Cincinnati.

programme.title: Beef Lamb Pig
programme.desc: Guy hunts down all kinds of meaty favorites from cottage pie to Asian-barbeque in Kentucky and North Carolina.

programme.title: Big Food Small Towns
programme.desc: Guy stops in small towns to dig in to big-time eats. In Raymond, NH, a butchery cranks out scratch-made corn dogs. In Rocky Hill, NJ, a 1700s inn turned gastropub dishes out a tomato twist on burgers and a spin on disco fries.

programme.title: Mega Mouthfuls
programme.desc: Guy unhinges his jaw for some mega-mouthful meals. In Louisville, KY, a funky seafood spot piles their specialties on top of waffles, and in Portland, OR, a killer barbecue food truck stacks a fully-loaded "shabamwich."

programme.title: Burgers Buns Bagels
programme.desc: This trip, Guy's picking up everything from burgers to buns to bagels. In Portsmouth, NH, a deli serves up lamb burgers and righteous ribs. In Los Angeles, a Koreatown favorite loads up Asian buns and a unique bacon-corn bar dish.

programme.title: The 1940s
programme.desc: War is the driving force behind much of the innovation in the 1940s. The microwave is born after a self-taught inventor realizes that military equipment is responsible for melting a chocolate bar in his pocket, and a sailor returns home and hits pay dirt with the invention of kitty litter.

programme.title: Darkness and Light
programme.desc: William's bold plan to infiltrate the Citadel goes awry when Leon is arrested after being caught talking to Alexim in the marketplace. Rather than executing Leon immediately, Kreel holds him prisoner as bait. Will William and the rebel forces fall to Kreel and Xax's nefarious plans?

programme.title: Separate Rooms
programme.desc: After years of hopes and prayers, and with their father's support, David and Ricky finally get to have their own separate bedrooms. Harriet, however, believes that deep down, Ozzie’s interest in the matter belies a deeper desire within Ozzie himself to also have his own bedroom.

programme.title: The Traffic Signal
programme.desc: After reading about an accident in the newspaper, the Nelson family debate over how they should proceed to request a traffic signal be installed at a dangerous intersection nearby. When a new traffic signal is quickly installed, the Nelsons are unsure who should get the credit, or the blame.

programme.title: The Speech
programme.desc: Ozzie painstakingly rehearses for a speech he is supposed to give at the local Chamber of Commerce. When an Army officer’s speech runs too long, Ozzie becomes greatly disappointed when his speech is bumped.

programme.title: Survival
programme.desc: A raging storm maroons the close-knit Robinson family and a band of shipwrecked survivors on a remote desert island, but they are not alone! Parsons, a sailor, blames David Robinson for his brother's death, and vows revenge. The family builds a tree house to guard against the island's dangers.

programme.title: The Night the Roof Fell In
programme.desc: Both Rob and Laura each experienced an unpleasant day, and it only gets worse when they meet at home for further argument. Only their pet goldfish, and their apartments four walls, can report the truth as Laura and Rob spin colorful, self-aggrandizing versions to their friends about their argument.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car Dennis heads to Delavan, WI for The Cars That Time Forgot.

programme.title: Body Surfer; The Rosenblatt Love Story; Dream Child; Soul Sister; Dog Rescues Cat
programme.desc: A drummer is miraculously rescued after snapping his neck at the bottom of the ocean. Two girls' psychic connection may have enabled one girl to wake the other from a coma. A rescued dog gave his adopted owner a reason to live again. And many more stories proving the existence of miracles.

programme.title: River Wild; Man in White; New Jersey Lake; Twister Survival; 1,000 Men and a Baby
programme.desc: Three girls crash through thin ice into freezing water, a man tries to come to their rescue when he too falls through the ice. Firefighters race against time to save all four lives as the whole thing is caught on tape. A 12-year-old boy hiking in the woods was critically bitten by a rattlesnake.

programme.title: Survival
programme.desc: A raging storm maroons the close-knit Robinson family and a band of shipwrecked survivors on a remote desert island, but they are not alone! Parsons, a sailor, blames David Robinson for his brother's death, and vows revenge. The family builds a tree house to guard against the island's dangers.

programme.title: Temptation's Run
programme.desc: The year is 1888, and Jess finds himself competing in a friendly race and interacting with the inhabitants of a small gold mining community, including an innocent immigrant named Tugen. Behind the scenes, however, something more malicious may be unfolding that requires Jess's intervention.

programme.title: A Dream of Flying
programme.desc: It is modern times, and following a crippling accident, Anna, a former teen horse riding prodigy, and her family visit a campground where Jess is working for the summer. Initially, Anna and Jess clash, but eventually they become friends, and Jess is able to inspire Anna to remember to hope.

programme.title: The Law of Moises
programme.desc: Moises, a talented young filmmaker, discovers that his true destiny is to save the town that he desires so much to escape. The question Moises longs to receive clarity on is- Do we choose our dreams, or do our dreams choose us?

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car, Dennis fires up a couple of Olds pace cars.

programme.title: My Classic Car
programme.desc: On this episode of My Classic Car Dennis heads to Delavan, WI for The Cars That Time Forgot.

programme.title: Hidden Valley
programme.desc: The group seeks refuge in the Hidden Valley, but they soon discover that the water supply has been contaminated with a powerful hypnotic substance that has turned the once peaceful village into an army of willing slaves. William is positive Xax and Kreel are behind it all.

programme.title: The Tomb of the Unknown Warrior
programme.desc: Will and the band are on a diplomatic mission to Mendica where two rival tribes, the Mendicans and the Sarks, have been fighting. Will is worried that the two tribes are too busy feuding to understand the threat of Xax's Warriors.

programme.title: The Lotus Eaters
programme.desc: After fleeing the Xaxian Warriors, William, and fellow rebels stumble upon the Sacred Valley, a place of startling natural beauty that seems to magically grant their every desire. Suddenly, the group quickly forgets about their quest for the Crystal Arrow, as something dangerous lurks about.

programme.title: Made for Each Other
programme.desc: Newlyweds, John and Jane Mason, struggle through their first year a marriage, plagued by money problems, illness, and a meddlesome live-in mother-in-law. To top it all off, their baby son is dying of pneumonia, and can only be saved by a serum that must be flown from Salt Lake City to New York.

programme.title: A Cat and Mouse Game
programme.desc: A family and their cat, Marcel, encounter a pet mouse (Cheeky) left behind by the former residents of a summer cottage. Like the classic comedy series, “Tom and Jerry”, Marcel watches and attempts to capture the mischievous Cheeky who constantly eludes him. What will become of the chase in time?

programme.title: A Crack in Time
programme.desc: The Johnson family's peaceful dairy farm life is turned upside down when the youngest son, David, wakes up to find a strange teenage girl in his closet. Her name is Jem Johnson, and she claims to be from the year 2098.

programme.title: Charlie

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.desc: Tackling largemouth bass in gin-clear water. Refine your tackle and tactics to eliminate any negative cues.

Rob Fordyce and his former mentor, Flip, share a flats boat, as they cast toward the mangroves in pursuit of some of their favorite game fish: snook, grouper and the silver king - tarpon.

programme.title: Wyoming Trout
programme.desc: "Like all Americans," said Theodore Roosevelt, "I like big things. Big prairies, big forests and mountains." And one of the big places he loved was Wyoming. Now for Ford's Fishing Frontiers co-host Preston Sharp and friends, it's a chance to fish for big trout in the Cowboy State.

programme.title: Cedar Lake Skis
programme.desc: Cedar Lake in Perrault Falls, Ontario, Canada, is a diverse musky fishery with multiple water colors and structural elements. Jim Saric and musky hunter Bob Turgeon grind through post-frontal conditions and sift through shallow cover utilizing boatside tactics to trigger Cedar Lake Skis to bite.

programme.title: Burning Up the Bay
programme.desc: The Great Lakes are home to some of the best musky fisheries across North America. In summer, the muskies often establish a home range around large, shallow weed flats. Jim Saric and Pro Guide Bret Alexander encountered a pack of muskies on an overcast and rainy summer day and with the biometrics being high, they burned blades covering water quickly, trigging strikes from multiple muskies.

programme.desc: Dr. Kroll is headed to the Sooner State with a muzzleloader to hunt with Tom Boyer of Boss Buck, then he and Pat give tips on managing your cedars, Haynes Shelton discusses arrow penetration and Jeremy Moore closes his three part series on shed dogs.

programme.title: Duck Opener (SCWA)
programme.desc: Chef Scott Leysath gets to shoot some ducks with his friends in the South Carolina Waterfowl Association. Susie Jimenez, Brad Fenson, Melissa Bachman, Cee Dub, and Buddy T pitch in with cooking and hunting tips.

programme.title: The Reluctant Gar Fisherman
programme.desc: Derek goes to Texas in search of the prehistoric looking alligator gar. Featuring Kirk Kirkland.

programme.title: Missouri Mega Blind
programme.desc: The hunt for ducks starts in southern Missouri in a mega blind that’s the stuff of waterfowl dreams.

programme.title: Trolling Up Musky
programme.desc: Fall trolling for muskies on Lake of the Woods in northwest Ontario. Maintain large lures in the fish zone

programme.title: Vermillion Walleye

programme.title: Ford Frontier Fishing
programme.desc: There are fishermen in this world; wise fishermen, expert fishermen, wonderfully skilled fishermen, and then there is Lefty Kreh. For over 60 years Lefty has been the fisherman's fisherman - more important though are all the years that Flip Pallot has been able to call him, simply - friend. They take on bass in the back waters of eastern Texas on this episode of Fishing Frontiers.
